    <h1>Is&#xAD;rael headed for sec&#xAD;ond lock&#xAD;down</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200912/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-12"><time>2020-09-12</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• Is­rael will en­ter a sec­ond coronaviru­s lock­down, be­com­ing the only de­vel­oped coun­try to shut down again na­tion­wide af­ter a botched re­open­ing of the econ­omy sent in­fec­tions soar­ing.</p>
    <p>An in­ner Cab­i­net of min­is­ters has ap­proved a two-week, full-fledged lock­down, to be fol­lowed by two more weeks of strict restric­tions on move­ment and eco­nomic ac­tiv­ity.</p>
    <p>Af­ter that, if the sit­u­a­tion im­proves, lim­i­ta­tions will be ap­plied only to com­mu­ni­ties with large out­breaks.</p>
    <p>De­tails, such as the start date, are to be sub­mit­ted to the full Cab­i­net for fi­nal ap­proval to­mor­row.</p>


